   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Research</span><hr size=1> Ok...first off bookmarked the site...has much potential! <BR>  <BR> Second <BR>  <BR> Research..... <BR>  <BR> I think a definitive guide on research items is important.  We all know that words drop off most mobs of the appropriate level, but where do you find things like ice of vellious? <BR>  <BR> I always check merchants and sometimes I get lucky.  Last night I found frost giant toes in Halas, I guess this makes sense.  Cost me 21 pp but at lvl 22 I will not be killing a frost giant anytime soon....  But I am new to the research game and could really use some help here.  Should I just cruise to the areas where the mobs are and hit the merchants there in hopes someone has sold the item, like hill giant toes or are there merchants that stock this stuff?  This goes for the Sol Ro quests too! <BR>  <BR> Thanks <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umellifleur.showPublicProfile>Mellifleur</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/7/00 6:50:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Research</span><hr size=1> Mage components are generally hard to come by and often your fellow adventurers will try to sell them to you for insane prices. <BR> I always check merchants in a hunting area,sometimes I find really good stuff there(Words of Convocation). <BR> So,if you are looking for spell components in the lvl range 29-34,RatheMtns gypsies pretty often have neat things sold to them by other players. <BR> Some merchants at the mage guilds sell research components(Scent of Marr,Breath of Ro)as well. <BR> Never leave an npc merchant unchecked ;) <BR>  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Dyscharge</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/7/00 8:06:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Research</span><hr size=1> Is there a way in which we can practice our research?  I tried to put all my 70 + training points towards research but I can only put 1 point per lvl.  Therefore when I when to make my level 16 pets...I failed on all 3 pets.  And can someone please tell me where I can find a Halas Heater?  Used for the lvl 16 fire elemental research...Any input would help.  Thanks !! <BR>  <BR> Dyscharge <BR> level 19 gnomish magician  <BR> Povar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umellifleur.showPublicProfile>Mellifleur</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/7/00 8:22:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Practice research</span><hr size=1> Until lvl 20 you can only train one point per lvl at your guild.After that you can put 5 per lvl into it. <BR> There is a practice research,if you are a DarkElf you need to go to SouthRo and give a gyspy and GreaterLightStone.She will then give you a Concordance of Research with that you can practice research.Should you be member of a &quot;good&quot; race you need to travel to NorthKaranas.There will be a gypsy as well to whom to give the Lightstone. <BR> Little hint:Dont research the lvl16 and lvl 20 pets,they are *all* for sale in the Ocean of Tears. <BR> If you come from Freeport,leave the ship at the first stop.Turn 90 degrees left from the pier and swim that way(not very long swim).You will come to an isle with a tower on it.A merchant is in the tower that will sell all lvl16 and 20 pets as well as some other summon spells.Watch out,since sometimes a Seafury cyclops roams around on the isle. <BR>  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> volt9</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/7/00 8:26:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   research</span><hr size=1> I'm 19 too, and I just don't bother with research. I've found that most of the spells I need can be bought in either mage guilds or ocean of tears. I'm planning on waiting past the point where you can only put 1 point into the skill. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Aesop</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/7/00 9:29:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   My thoughts and contributions...</span><hr size=1> First thing-- and this is second-hand info, though from a good friend and guildmate who claims he's seen this himself.  Some of the vendors sell harder-to-find research components on a regular basis.  Supposedly, one can buy all the Ice of Velios one could ever want from a certain dwarven merchant in Dagnor's Caldron.  I've never seen this myself, but I do intend to check the next time I'm in the area-- I finally got my water pet, and won't need one for the next circle. <BR>  <BR> Second-- different guild merchants seem to have different pets, so far at least two per circle.  For example, for 29, it's fire and earth (I think)-- water I definitely had to research all the way from 20 (bought 'em from OOT). Still, this means one should keep an eye on what pets come at the next circle, particularly if it ISN'T the only pet you tend to use. <BR>  <BR> Third-- practice, practice, practice!  The higher the level, the harder the components are to come by, and the more one NEEDS to practice.  Just because you've no use for the HUNDREDS of words of tyranny you have doesn't mean you shouldn't practice level 20 spells until they triv-- you'll be glad you did come higher levels! <BR>  <BR> Fourth-- and along the same vein-- the Concordance Quest.  I'm looking for info on the triv levels for various spells.  Unfortunately, I'm already up to 64 in Research, so I won't be contributing the lower levels, but that makes it DARNED hard to know for what level research I should start collecting items (Journeyman?  Initiate?).  I'll be doing a post for this next. <BR>  <BR> -Aesop <BR> The Multi-Purpose Magician <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uzanzabar.showPublicProfile>Zanzabar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/8/00 6:46:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: My thoughts and contributions...</span><hr size=1> My advice is not to wait to research. I did and still reget it. If you dont want to spend precious traing point on it then use the Practice Concourse. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Fallawen Farwalker</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/8/00 6:46:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Ice of Velious</span><hr size=1> I founb the ice on the treants in SK,3 times so far. <BR>  <BR> -Fallawen Farwalker <BR>  25th Magician <BR>  Solusek Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/udabones.showPublicProfile>DaBones</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/8/00 8:02:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Ice of Velious</span><hr size=1> I agree, don't wait to start research.  I waited till 30's to start -- that was WAY too late.  You ARE gonna want/need those pets later ... <BR>  <BR>  <BR> Lvl50 Mage <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Mingna</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/14/00 6:46:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Research-newbie advocate</span><hr size=1> I agree that a resource guidebook for research with a self-help style  would be a great idea. (You go Everwind !) But it should be opened up with an overview of what research is and how it will affect your game strategy. This will let newbies know what they are preparing for and why they're saving up those training points. And then explain what to start using them on and when. That would be great ! Forewarned is forearmed. Y'know ? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unabienincinerador.showPublicProfile>Nabien Incinerador</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(2/15/00 12:48:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Research-newbie advocate</span><hr size=1> You can buy all your pets up to 20 or 24 in OOT.  Heatstone and coldstone you can find in the libraries. <BR>  <BR> Don't wait to start research, I just use my training points to train to the max every level... no real use for them other than this. <BR>  <BR> Nabien <BR> 32nd level magi <BR> The Stone Cutters <BR> Povar. <BR>  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Quale</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(3/7/00 6:39:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Practice research. Newbies check this out!</span><hr size=1> Patience and timing, it is everything for the one who wishes to pursue the secrets of the arcane.<br>
<br>
But even to such a soul, the prospect of going through all the motions of practicing in addition to doing the actual research can be daunting to say the least.<br>
<br>
At level 24 I found myself at the point where the issue could not be postponed any further. <br>
I got an overview of the materials needed and got the practice tome from the gypsy by trading away my beloved greater lightstone which I was fortunate to have by coincidence from before. <br>
I had the recipes from somewhere in these boards that claimed to be nearly 100% correct and not without expectation I made an attempt to make my very first azla practice rune. It failed. Obviously the very first recipe of the very first practice rune was false.<br>
I sat back and started to sweat.<br>
I was afraid I maybe had to run all the way back to the gypsies from my beloved Ak'Anon to get the recipe books, but I wasn't gonna give up that easy.<br>
So I did a /who using magician filter and started to tell the first few high level mages I could find to politely ask if they knew the recipes for the first few practice runes. <br>
After having talked to many a friendly mage ranging from 30 to some 40 levels, the conclusion could not be more unanimous.<br>
None of them knew anything about practice research because none of them had ever had any use for it.<br>
What they all had done was simply to pour the maximum number of practice points into the research skill at their guild trainers and started researching.<br>
Luckily I have always been extremely stingy with my practice points and had over 80 of them left myself.<br>
I saw a way to get out of the would be extremely time consuming and maybe even class discouraging process of research practice and went ahead and poured the max allowed points into my research skill. The very first research I attempted was everfount and I was successful at my first try.<br>
<br>
I don't think I will ever practice research except through the actual researching itself, and boy am I glad!<br>
<br>
Snifnix lvl 25 gnome mage Mith Marr. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uezno.showPublicProfile>Ezno</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Global user</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(3/9/00 10:00:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlibrarysubmissions.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Practice research. Newbies check this out!</span><hr size=1> <br>
