<br>
All your other skills can be easily improved with some simple practice sessions (casting over and over).  Research training requires hours of hunting or searching for the right components (especially at the higher training levels) to get a shot at improving your skill.<br>
<br>
It's easier and takes less time to just save your training points as you level up, and invest them later in life in your research skill.<br>
<br>
I've played all 4 INT-caster classes, and IMO the mage has the most difficult-to-obtain research components of any of them (barring a very few ultra-rare runes, pages, etc.).  Compounded with the need to re-research the LAST circle of spells to get a component to the NEW circle of spells!<br>
